{"title_page": "Helicocranchia pfefferi", "text_new": "{{short description|Species of mollusk}}\n{{pp-move-indef|small=yes}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| name = Banded piglet squid\n| status = DD\n| status_system = IUCN3.1\n| status_ref = <ref name = IUCN>{{cite iucn | author1 = Barratt, I. | author2-link = Louise Allcock | author2 = Allcock, L. | year = 2014 | title = ''Helicocranchia pfefferi'' | volume = 2014 | page = e.T162906A951921 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.2014-1.RLTS.T162906A951921.en}} Downloaded on 01 March 2018.</ref>\n| image = Helicopfefferidraw2.jpg\n| image_caption = Ventral view of a specimen taken off [[Southern California]] (41 mm ML)\n| taxon = Helicocranchia pfefferi\n| display_parents = 3\n| authority = [[Anne Letitia Massy|Massy]], 1907<ref name = WoRMS>{{cite web | url = http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id=139424 | title = ''Helicocranchia pfefferi'' Massy, 1907 | accessdate = 1 March 2018 | publisher = Flanders Marine Institute | year = 2016 | author = Julian Finn | work = World Register of Marine Species}}</ref> \n| synonyms = ''Helicocranchia beebei'' <small>[[Guy Coburn Robson|Robson]], 1948</small>\n}}\n\n'''''Helicocranchia pfefferi''''', the '''banded piglet squid''', is a small [[squid]] of the genus ''[[Helicocranchia]]''. Adults of this species are [[Mesopelagic zone|mesopelaegic]].\n\n== Physical characteristics ==\nThe average size of adult ''H. pfefferi'' is {{convert|100|mm|in|abbr=on}} in [[mantle (mollusc)|mantle]] length (ML). The body consists of a large [[Hyponome|funnel]] with small paddle-like fins. They have small [[tentacle]]s above their eyes. The funnel does not have valves, but contains a  dorsal pad with three papillae as organs.{{Citation needed|date=October 2008}} Paddle-shaped fins are attached to a part of the [[Gladius (cephalopod)|gladius]]. ''H. pfefferi'' has a single ocular [[photophore]] and does not have photophores at its [[cephalopod arm|arm]] tips.\n\n== Habitat ==\n\nAs [[paralarva]]e (<30&nbsp;mm ML), they live near the surface of the oceans, between 100 m and 200 m deep. They descend to the [[mesopelagic zone]] as they mature, but do not exhibit a [[diel vertical migration]] pattern.<ref>{{cite journal |author=Lu, C.C. & M.R. Clarke |title=Vertical Distribution of Cephalopods at 11\u00b0 N 20\u00b0 W in the North Atlantic |journal=Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom |volume=55 |issue=2 |pages=369\u2013389 |year=1975 |doi=10.1017/S0025315400016003}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== Prey ==\nIt is considered to have the same diet as most squids such as fish, shrimp, and squid.\n\n* Young, R.E. & K.M. Mangold (1922-2003). 2006. [http://tolweb.org/Helicocranchia/19550 ''Helicocranchia'' Massy, 1907]. Version 16 July 2006 (under construction). In: The Tree of Life Web Project.\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Helicocranchia pfefferi}}\n{{CephBase Species|444}}\n* [http://archive.serpentproject.com/160/ Images of ''Helicocranchia'' from the SERPENT Project]\n* [http://seawayblog.blogspot.com/2009/01/piglet-squid-into-abyss-lives-squid.html Blog post with lots of information]\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q2366378}}\n\n[[Category:Squid]]\n[[Category:Molluscs described in 1907]]\n[[Category:Taxa named by Annie Massy]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-move-indef|small=yes}}\n{{Speciesbox\n| name = Banded piglet squid\n| status = DD\n| status_system = IUCN3.1\n| status_ref = <ref name = IUCN>{{cite iucn | author1 = Barratt, I. | author2-link = Louise Allcock | author2 = Allcock, L. | year = 2014 | title = ''Helicocranchia pfefferi'' | volume = 2014 | page = e.T162906A951921 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.2014-1.RLTS.T162906A951921.en}} Downloaded on 01 March 2018.</ref>\n| image = Helicopfefferidraw2.jpg\n| image_caption = Ventral view of a specimen taken off [[Southern California]] (41 mm ML)\n| taxon = Helicocranchia pfefferi\n| display_parents = 3\n| authority = [[Anne Letitia Massy|Massy]], 1907<ref name = WoRMS>{{cite web | url = http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id=139424 | title = ''Helicocranchia pfefferi'' Massy, 1907 | accessdate = 1 March 2018 | publisher = Flanders Marine Institute | year = 2016 | author = Julian Finn | work = World Register of Marine Species}}</ref> \n| synonyms = ''Helicocranchia beebei'' <small>[[Guy Coburn Robson|Robson]], 1948</small>\n}}\n\n'''''Helicocranchia pfefferi''''', the '''banded piglet squid''', is a small [[squid]] of the genus ''[[Helicocranchia]]''. Adults of this species are [[Mesopelagic zone|mesopelaegic]].\n\n== Physical characteristics ==\nThe average size of adult ''H. pfefferi'' is {{convert|100|mm|in|abbr=on}} in [[mantle (mollusc)|mantle]] length (ML). The body consists of a large [[Hyponome|funnel]] with small paddle-like fins. They have small [[tentacle]]s above their eyes. The funnel does not have valves, but contains a  dorsal pad with three papillae as organs.{{Citation needed|date=October 2008}} Paddle-shaped fins are attached to a part of the [[Gladius (cephalopod)|gladius]]. ''H. pfefferi'' has a single ocular [[photophore]] and does not have photophores at its [[cephalopod arm|arm]] tips.\n\n== Habitat ==\n\nAs [[paralarva]]e (<30&nbsp;mm ML), they live near the surface of the oceans, between 100 m and 200 m deep. They descend to the [[mesopelagic zone]] as they mature, but do not exhibit a [[diel vertical migration]] pattern.<ref>{{cite journal |author=Lu, C.C. & M.R. Clarke |title=Vertical Distribution of Cephalopods at 11\u00b0 N 20\u00b0 W in the North Atlantic |journal=Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom |volume=55 |issue=2 |pages=369\u2013389 |year=1975 |doi=10.1017/S0025315400016003}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== Prey ==\nIt is considered to have the same diet as most squids such as fish, shrimp, and squid.\n\n* Young, R.E. & K.M. Mangold (1922-2003). 2006. [http://tolweb.org/Helicocranchia/19550 ''Helicocranchia'' Massy, 1907]. Version 16 July 2006 (under construction). In: The Tree of Life Web Project.\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Helicocranchia pfefferi}}\n{{CephBase Species|444}}\n* [http://archive.serpentproject.com/160/ Images of ''Helicocranchia'' from the SERPENT Project]\n* [http://seawayblog.blogspot.com/2009/01/piglet-squid-into-abyss-lives-squid.html Blog post with lots of information]\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q2366378}}\n\n[[Category:Squid]]\n[[Category:Molluscs described in 1907]]\n[[Category:Taxa named by Annie Massy]]\n", "name_user": "Stickymatch", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Adding localshort description: \"Species of mollusk\", overriding Wikidata description \"species of mollusc\" (Shortdesc helper))", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helicocranchia_pfefferi"}
