y]]<ref>{{cite news|title=U.S. hikers in Iran get 8 years in prison, state media reports|url=http://www.cnn.com/2011/WORLD/meast/08/20/iran.us.hikers/|agency=CNN|date=21 August 2011}}</ref>\n* August 24 \u2013 [[Kim Jong-il]] initiated rare talks with Russian Prime Minister [[Dmitry Medvedev]], speaks about possibility of denuclearisation and economic cooperation<ref>{{cite news|title=Kim Jong-il in talks with Russia's Dmitry Medvedev\n|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-pacific-14600366|agency=BBC|date=24 August 2011}}</ref>\n* August 29 \u2013 Libyan leader [[Muammar Gaddafi]] flees to [[Algeria]] with his wife and three children<ref>{{cite news|title=Libya conflict: Gaddafi family 'flee to Algeria'|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-14712242|agency=BBC|date=29 August 2011}}</ref>\n* August 29 - [[Toomas Hendrik Ilves]] is re-elected [[President of Estonia]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Estonian President Ilves re-elected|url=https://sg.news.yahoo.com/estonian-president-ilves-elected-120335745.html|agency=Yahoo News|date=29 August 2011}}</ref>\n* August 30 \u2013 Japan's governing party, the [[Democratic Party of Japan]], votes [[Yoshihiko Noda]] as leader<ref>{{cite news|title=Yoshihiko Noda wins Japan leadership race|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-pacific-14705394|agency=BBC|date=30 August 2011}}</ref>\n* August 31 \u2013 Libyan Rebels issue ultimatum to troops still loyal to [[Muammar Qaddafi]], rebels say loyalists must surrender or face an attack<ref>{{cite news|title=Libya rebels give Qaddafi loyalists an ultimatum|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/libya-rebels-give-qaddafi-loyalists-an-ultimatum/|agency=CBSNews|date=31 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n===September===\n\n<!--[[File:Wall-Street-1.jpg|thumb|Occupy Wall Street Poster]]-->\n* September 2 \u2013 [[Turkey]] expels Israeli diplomats in protest over Israeli raid on Gaza-bound ship, in which 9 Turkish nationals died<ref>{{cite news|title=Turkey expels Israeli diplomats after UN report|url=https://