l Street Protest Begins, With Demonstrators Blocked |publisher= City Room (blog of [[The New York Times]]) |date= September 17, 2011 |accessdate= October 16, 2011}}</ref>\n* September 21 \u2013 [[2009\u201311 detention of American hikers by Iran|Hikers detained in Iran are freed]]{{Citation needed|date=January 2017}}\n* September 23 \u2013 [[Yemen]]i President [[Ali Abdullah Saleh]] returns from emergency medical treatment in [[Saudi Arabia]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Yemen President Ali Abdullah Saleh returns to Sanaa|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-15030899|agency=BBC|date=23 September 2011}}</ref>\n* September 24 \u2013 [[State of Palestine|Palestine]] leader [[Mahmoud Abbas]] submits request to the [[United Nations]] to be recognized as a state<ref>{{cite news|title=YIsraeli-Palestinian talks must resume&nbsp;\u2014 Mideast Quartet|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-15044601|agency=BBC|date=24 September 2011}}</ref>\n* September 24 \u2013 [[Vladimir Putin]] is set to return as Russia's President in 2012, [[Dmitry Medvedev]] the current President, will switch positions with Putin to become the Prime Minister<ref>{{cite news|title=Russia's Putin set to return as president in 2012|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-15045816|agency=BBC|date=24 September 2011}}</ref>\n* September 25 \u2013 Women in [[Saudi Arabia]] gain the right to vote and to stand for election<ref>{{cite news|last1=MacFarquhar|first1=Neil|title=Saudi Monarch Grants Women Right to Vote|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/09/26/world/middleeast/women-to-vote-in-saudi-arabia-king-says.html|agency=New York Times|date=25 September 2011}}</ref>\n* September 29 \u2013 Eurozone bailout fund is granted expanded powers in an attempt to stabilize the Euro<ref>{{cite news|title=Euro fund expansion passed by German parliament|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/business/euro-fund-expansion-passed-by-german-parliament-1.1083348|agency=CBC|date=29 September 2011}}</ref>\n\n===October===\n\n[[File:Flickr - Israel Defense Forces - Gilad Shalit Salutes Israel Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.jpg|thumb|Gilad Shalit Salutes Israel Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu]]\n[[File:Julian Assange August 2014.jpg|thumb|Julian Assange]]\n* October 2 \u2013 Greece is set to default on a bailout package despite austerity measures, the bailout package is less than a year old<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kyriakidou|first1=Dina|last2=Melander|first2=Ingrid|title=Greece to miss deficit targets despite austerity|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-greece-idUSTRE7900SU20111002|agency=CBC|date=2 October 2011}}</ref>\n* October 8 \u2013 Yemen's President [[Ali Abdullah Saleh]] promises to cede power, a promise he has made 3 times in 2011<ref>{{cite news|title=Saleh keeps Yemenis guessing with talk of step-down|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-yemen-saleh-idUSTRE7970W420111008|agency=Reuteurs|date=8 October 2011}}</ref>\n* October 8 \u2013 Security council vetoes 2 resolutions on Syria, the drafts would have stopped aerial bombardment, the other would have urged a halt to hostilities<ref>{{cite news|title=Security Council Fails to Adopt Two Draft Resolutions on Syria, Despite Appeals for Action Preventing Impending Humanitarian Catastrophe in Aleppo|url=https://www.un.org/press/en/2016/sc12545.doc.htm|agency=UN|date=8 October 2011}}</ref>\n* October 9 \u2013 23 people die amid clashes between [[Egyptian military|Egyptian Security Forces]] and protesters<ref>{{cite news|title=At Least 23 Dead As Egyptian Forces Clash With Protesters|url=http://www.wibw.com/home/headlines/At_least_23_dead_as_Egyptian_forces_clash_with_protesters_131428008.html|agency=WIBW|date=9 October 2011}}</ref>\n* October 9 \u2013 Germany's [[Merkel]] and France's [[Sarkozy]] agree to important changes to the way the [[Eurozone]] operates, in an attempt to end Euro crisis<ref>{{cite news|title=Eurozone crisis: Merkel and Sarkozy 'agree key changes'|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-15226953|agency=BBC|date=9 October 2011}}</ref>\n* October 11 \u2013 [[Gilad Shalit prisoner exchange|Israel and Hamas agree to a prisoner swap]], 1000 Palestinian prisoners for Israeli soldier Gilad Shalit<ref>{{cite news|title=Israel and Hamas agree prisoner swap to free Shalit|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-israel-palestinians-shalit-idUSTRE79A58R20111011|agency=Reuters|date=11 October 2011}}</ref>\n* October 15 \u2013 At least 70 people are injured in Rome, as protesters clash with police, amid protests inspired by [[Occupy Wall Street]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Rome protest against cuts descends into violence|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-pacific-15319924|agency=BBC|date=15 October 2011}}</ref>\n* October 15 \u2013 Protesters from [[Occupy Wall Street]] move to fill Time's Square<ref>{{cite news|title=Thousands of protesters fill NYC's Times Square|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/thousands-of-protesters-fill-nycs-times-square/|agency=CBSNews|date=15 October 2011}}</ref>\n* October 17 \u2013 [[Francois Hollande]] wins primary race of the [[French Socialist Party]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Crumley|first1=Bruce|title=Hollande Wins French Socialist Primary, Looks to the Battle Ahead with Sarkozy|url=http://world.time.com/2011/10/17/francois-hollande-wins-french-socialist-presidential-primary-and-looks-towards-the-real-battle-with-sarkozy/|agency=Time|date=17 October 2011}}</ref>\n* October 22 \u2013 Heir to Saudi throne [[Abdul Aziz Al Saud]] dies at 85<ref>{{cite news|title=Saudi Arabia's Crown Prince Sultan bin Abdul Aziz Al Saud Dies|url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2011/10/22/saudi-arabias-crown-prince-sultan-bin-abdul-aziz-al-saud-has-died.html|agency=CBSNews|date=22 October 2011}}</ref>\n* October 23 \u2013 [[Libya|Libya's]] interim leaders declare liberation from the [[Gaddafi regime]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Libya's new leaders declare liberation|url=http://www.cnn.com/2011/10/23/world/africa/libya-main/|agency=CNN|date=23 October 2011}}</ref>\n* October 24 \u2013 