a's [[FARC]] name [[Timoleon Jimenez]] as new leader<ref>{{cite news|title=Colombia's FARC rebels pick hardline new leader|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-colombia-rebels-idUSTRE7AE23E20111115|agency=Reuters|date=15 November 2011}}</ref>\n* November 18 \u2013 Hundreds of people are arrested as [[Occupy Wall Street]] protesters march across the Brooklyn Bridge<ref>{{cite news|title=Mass arrests at Occupy Wall Street protests|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-15784439|agency=BBC|date=18 November 2011}}</ref>\n* November 18 \u2013 The UN's nuclear watchdog voices deep concern over [[Iranian Nuclear program]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Iran nuclear: UN voices 'deep concern' over plans|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-15797177|agency=BBC|date=18 November 2011}}</ref>\n* November 20 \u2013 The [[People's Party (Spain)|People's Party]] of [[Spain]] win election in a landslide<ref>{{cite news|title=Spain's conservatives win election in landslide|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/spain-s-conservatives-win-election-in-landslide-1.1042493|agency=CBC|date=20 November 2011}}</ref>\n* November 24 \u2013 [[Egyptian military]] appoint new Prime Minister [[Kamal Ganzouri]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Egypt military 'appoints Kamal Ganzouri as new PM'|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-15883031|agency=BBC|date=24 November 2011}}</ref>\n* November 28 \u2013 First day of Egyptian elections since the military seized power<ref>{{cite news|title=Polls close after first day of Egyptian elections|url=http://www.cnn.com/2011/11/28/world/africa/egypt-elections/|agency=CNN|date=28 November 2011}}</ref>\n* November 29 \u2013 Protesters in [[Iran]] [[2011 attack on the British Embassy in Iran|storm the British embassy in Tehran]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Iran protesters storm UK embassy in Tehran|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-15936213|agency=BBC|date=29 November 2011}}</ref>\n* November 30 \u2013 The [[UK]] expels all Iranian diplomats from country, 